import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'], label='S&P 500 Stock Prices')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.title('What is the trend of S&P 500 stock prices over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['price'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Price')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of S&P 500 stock prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    average_price = data['price'].mean()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'], label='S&P 500 Stock Price')
    plt.axhline(y=average_price, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Price: {average_price:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.title('What is the average S&P 500 stock price over the given time period?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.boxplot(data['price'])
    plt.title('What is the volatility of S&P 500 stock prices?')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.xticks([1], ['S&P 500'])
    plt.legend(['Price'], loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
